#compdef tawk
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# shawnw/tawk tawk (**Tcl language**; uses tcllib's
# `cmdline::getoptions` library; first documented Tcl
# `cmdline` CLI in the corpus):
#   tawk lines 25-29 (`package require Tcl 8.6;
#     package require dicttool; package require
#     textutil::split; package require cmdline; package
#     require csv` — declares dependency on tcllib's
#     `cmdline` module)
#   tawk lines 480-489
#     (`set options { {f.arg "" "Filename..."}
#     {F.arg whitespace "Field separator."} {csv
#     "Input is CSV data."} {quoteall "Always quote
#     CSV fields."} {quotechar.arg \" "Use this
#     character to quote CSV fields."} {safe "Execute
#     script in safe mode."} {timeout.arg 0 "Error if
#     script takes more than N seconds..."} {version
#     "Print version."} }` — Tcl LIST-of-LISTS option
#     spec; 8 entries)
